{
  "texts": [
    "Nevertheless, if we restrict to considering correlation functions of physical states that are formed only from application of the operators ∂ X j n and Ψ A,j r, then we can generalise our statements about which terms are non-vanishing in (B.1).",
    "In particular, there will be no non-vanishing contributions from insertions including G-C as before.",
    "If we insert ∂ X j n, then the argument above is completely unchanged, as this operator contains no additional ghost contribution.",
    "By contrast, the operator Ψ A,j r is in picture P = -1, so we need to be careful with charge conservation.",
    "There are no new contributions for the σ-ghost, so the only possible contributing terms persist to be -iσ from G -, (-2ρ -iσ -iH) from G-, (ρ + iH) from G+ and the ghosts of the physical states."
  ]
}